climbs.name: Baker's Dozen
climbs.fa: drilled by TLusk in 1995 but never sent.

content.description:
Half pad diagonal edges with no feet mark the start of the 15 foot crux. Tony Lusk drilled it for me because he was pretty sure he couldnt do it. Route is slightly overhung.

 A crumbling crux hold and the difficulty of recruiting belayers made me abort the project.
content.location: The blank east face of Mystery has a line of bolts.

content.description:
Small pinnacle in middle of Outback with a few routes. 

  When we got on top of the pinnacle in 1995 we found a couple of bolts that looked ANCIENT even then.  Who put them in ??  John Rupley ?  I don't know. 

  I have an old project on the steep blank east face that I may resurrect.
